Law enforcers of the city are currently (Friday) awaiting the arrival of Police Minister Bheki Cele.
Police officers as well as provincial and municipal traffic officers and members of the army are gathered in front of the Polokwane Police Station.
It was learnt that Cele is expected to visit certain locations in and around Polokwane as well as in Tzaneen to ensure that Covid-19 regulations are being adhered to.
His findings during the visit will be made available later today.
Story: RC Myburgh